Microsoft is planning to <a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/12/24294652/microsoft-windows-11-mail-calendar-apps-end-of-support">no longer support</a> the Windows Mail, Calendar, and People apps later this year. The Verge:<i> The software giant has been moving existing users of these apps over to the new Outlook for Windows app in recent months, and now it has set an end of support date for the Mail, Calendar, and People apps of December 31st.<br> <br>
