<div><div><aside data-gu-name="matchNav"></aside><aside data-gu-name="matchtabs"></aside><div data-gu-name="media"><div><div><div><img alt="The Bluesky social media app logo" src="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/867d786ca5c59d9a8e849f75d4f0518a51d11106/0_396_6048_3628/master/6048.jpg?width=465&amp;dpr=1&amp;s=none&amp;crop=none"><span><div><div><label for="the-checkbox"><svg fill="white" viewBox="0 0 6 14"><path d="M4.6 12l-.4 1.4c-.7.2-1.9.6-3 .6-.7 0-1.2-.2-1.2-.9 0-.2 0-.3.1-.5l2-6.7H.7l.4-1.5 4.2-.6h.2L3 12h1.6zm-.3-9.2c-.9 0-1.4-.5-1.4-1.3C2.9.5 3.7 0 4.6 0 5.4 0 6 .5 6 1.3c0 1-.8 1.5-1.7 1.5z"></path></svg></label><input type="checkbox"> <div><figcaption data-spacefinder-role="inline"><span><svg viewBox="0 0 18 13"><path d="M18 3.5v8l-1.5 1.5h-15l-1.5-1.5v-8l1.5-1.5h3.5l2-2h4l2 2h3.5l1.5 1.5zm-9 7.5c1.9 0 3.5-1.6 3.5-3.5s-1.6-3.5-3.5-3.5-3.5 1.6-3.5 3.5 1.6 3.5 3.5 3.5z"></path></svg></span><span>Bluesky has added 700,000 new users since the US election as people flee X, formerly known as Twitter.</span> Photograph: Jaap Arriens/NurPhoto/Shutterstock</figcaption></div></div></div></span><a href="#img-1" data-ignore="global-link-styling" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"><button data-element-id="c9f0bbe5-cb55-44ce-bf7f-f498289f2dfa" type="button" aria-haspopup="dialog"><svg viewBox="-3 -3 30 30" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M23 8.75V1.5l-.5-.5h-7.25v1.25l4.5.6L14 8.575 15.4 10l5.75-5.725.6 4.475zm-22 6.5v7.25l.475.5h7.25v-1.25l-4.475-.6 5.725-5.775L8.6 14l-5.775 5.725-.575-4.475z"></path></svg><span>View image in fullscreen</span></button></a></div><span><figcaption data-spacefinder-role="inline"><span><svg viewBox="0 0 18 13"><path d="M18 3.5v8l-1.5 1.5h-15l-1.5-1.5v-8l1.5-1.5h3.5l2-2h4l2 2h3.5l1.5 1.5zm-9 7.5c1.9 0 3.5-1.6 3.5-3.5s-1.6-3.5-3.5-3.5-3.5 1.6-3.5 3.5 1.6 3.5 3.5 3.5z"></path></svg></span><span>Bluesky has added 700,000 new users since the US election as people flee X, formerly known as Twitter.</span> Photograph: Jaap Arriens/NurPhoto/Shutterstock</figcaption></span></div></div></div><aside data-gu-name="title"><div><div><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/technology/bluesky" data-component="section" data-link-name="article section"><span>Bluesky</span></a></div></div></aside><div data-gu-name="border"></div><div data-gu-name="headline"><div><div><h1>Bluesky adds 700,000 new members as users flee X after the US election</h1></div></div></div><div data-gu-name="standfirst"><div><p>Social media platform has become a ‘refuge’ from the far-right activism on X, experts say, after Elon Musk teamed up with Donald Trump</p></div></div><aside data-gu-name="meta"><div><div><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 1300 13" preserveAspectRatio="none" stroke="var(--article-border)" stroke-width="1" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><line x1="0" x2="1300" y1="0.5" y2="0.5"></line><line x1="0" x2="1300" y1="4.5" y2="4.5"></line><line x1="0" x2="1300" y1="8.5" y2="8.5"></line><line x1="0" x2="1300" y1="12.5" y2="12.5"></line></svg></div></div><div><div><div><div><div><address aria-label="Contributor info" data-component="meta-byline" data-link-name="byline"><div><a data-link-name="auto tag link" href="https://www.theguardian.com/profile/luca-ittimani">Luca Ittimani</a></div></address><details><summary><span>Mon 11 Nov 2024 21.44 EST</span></summary>Last modified on Tue 12 Nov 2024 11.11 EST</details></div></div><div data-print-layout="hide"><div><gu-island name="ShareButton" priority="feature" deferuntil="visible" props="{&quot;pageId&quot;:&quot;technology/2024/nov/12/us-election-bluesky-users-flee-x-twitter-trump-musk&quot;,&quot;webTitle&quot;:&quot;Bluesky adds 700,000 new members as users flee X after the US election&quot;,&quot;format&quot;:{&quot;design&quot;:0,&quot;display&quot;:0,&quot;theme&quot;:0},&quot;context&quot;:&quot;ArticleMeta&quot;}"><a href="mailto:?subject=Bluesky adds 700,000 new members as users flee X after the US election&amp;body=https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2024/nov/12/us-election-bluesky-users-flee-x-twitter-trump-musk?CMP=share_btn_url" type="button">Share<svg viewBox="-3 -3 30 30" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M19 16c1.675 0 3 1.35 3 3 0 1.675-1.325 3-3 3a2.97 2.97 0 0 1-2.975-3c0-.125 0-.275.025-.375L7.1 14.15a2.9 2.9 0 0 1-2.075.825C3.325 14.975 2 13.65 2 12a3.004 3.004 0 0 1 3.025-3.025c.775 0 1.5.35 2.075.875l8.95-4.475c-.025-.1-.025-.225-.025-.4A2.966 2.966 0 0 1 19 2c1.675 0 3 1.325 3 2.975C22 6.65 20.675 8 19 8c-.8 0-1.475-.325-2.05-.825l-8.975 4.45C8 11.7 8 11.825 8 12s0 .3-.025.375l8.975 4.45c.575-.5 1.25-.825 2.05-.825m0-12.8c-.975 0-1.8.775-1.8 1.775S18.025 6.8 19 6.8c1 0 1.825-.825 1.825-1.825S20 3.2 19 3.2m0 17.6c1 0 1.825-.825 1.825-1.8 0-1-.825-1.8-1.825-1.8-.975 0-1.8.8-1.8 1.8 0 .975.825 1.8 1.8 1.8"></path></svg></a></gu-island></div></div></div></div></div><div><span><gu-island name="ExpandableMarketingCardWrapper" priority="enhancement" deferuntil="visible" props="{&quot;guardianBaseURL&quot;:&quot;https://www.theguardian.com&quot;}"></gu-island></span></div></aside><div data-gu-name="body"><span><gu-island name="ExpandableMarketingCardWrapper" priority="enhancement" deferuntil="idle" props="{&quot;guardianBaseURL&quot;:&quot;https://www.theguardian.com&quot;}"></gu-island></span><div><div><div><p>Social media platform <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/technology/bluesky" data-link-name="in body link">Bluesky</a> has picked up more than 700,000 new users in the week since the US election, as users seek to escape <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2024/oct/31/elon-musk-election-integrity-community-misinformation-disinformation" data-link-name="in body link">misinformation</a> and <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/media/2024/nov/04/chinese-americans-election-misinformation" data-link-name="in body link">offensive</a> posts on X.</p><p>The influx, largely from North America and the UK, has helped <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/technology/bluesky" data-link-name="in body link" data-component="auto-linked-tag">Bluesky</a> reach 14.5 million users worldwide, up from 9 million in September, the company said.</p><div><gu-island name="SignInGateSelector" priority="feature" deferuntil="visible" props="{&quot;contentType&quot;:&quot;Article&quot;,&quot;sectionId&quot;:&quot;technology&quot;,&quot;tags&quot;:[{&quot;id&quot;:&quot;technology/bluesky&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;Keyword&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Bluesky&quot;},{&quot;id&quot;:&quot;technology/twitter&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;Keyword&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;X&quot;},{&quot;id&quot;:&quot;technology/internet&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;Keyword&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Internet&quot;},{&quot;id&quot;:&quot;media/media&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;Keyword&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Media&quot;},{&quot;id&quot;:&quot;technology/technology&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;Keyword&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Technology&quot;},{&quot;id&quot;:&quot;us-news/us-elections-2024&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;Keyword&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;US elections 2024&quot;},{&quot;id&quot;:&quot;technology/elon-musk&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;Keyword&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Elon Musk&quot;},{&quot;id&quot;:&quot;type/article&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;Type&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Article&quot;},{&quot;id&quot;:&quot;tone/news&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;Tone&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;News&quot;},{&quot;id&quot;:&quot;profile/luca-ittimani&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;Contributor&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Luca Ittimani&quot;,&quot;bylineImageUrl&quot;:&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/uploads/2024/02/22/Luca_Ittimani.jpg?width=300&amp;quality=85&amp;auto=format&amp;fit=max&amp;s=2cb6eccd238b67f2f89f184286b427d5&quot;,&quot;bylineLargeImageUrl&quot;:&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/uploads/2024/02/22/Luca_Ittimani.png?width=3